      <chapter eId="chp_59_1">
        <num>Chapter 59-1</num>
        <heading>General Taxation Policies</heading>
        <section eId="sec_59_1_1002">
          <num>59-1-1002</num>
          <heading>Audit interviews.</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Effective 5/7/2025
59-1-1002.
Audit interviews.
(1)
During any audit interview, the commission shall:
(a)
require reasonable scheduling of its audit interviews;
(b)
permit recording of audit interviews;
(c)
explain its audit and collection process before the first interview; and
(d)
allow a taxpayer to be represented at an interview by an attorney or other representative with power of attorney.
(2)
The commission may not require a taxpayer to bring an attorney or other representative to interviews.
Amended by Chapter
302
, 2025 General Session</p>
          </content>
          <subsection eId="59_1_1002__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>During any audit interview, the commission shall:</p>
            </content>
            <paragraph eId="59_1_1002__subsec_1__para_a">
              <num>(a)</num>
              <content>
                <p>require reasonable scheduling of its audit interviews;</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="59_1_1002__subsec_1__para_b">
              <num>(b)</num>
              <content>
                <p>permit recording of audit interviews;</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="59_1_1002__subsec_1__para_c">
              <num>(c)</num>
              <content>
                <p>explain its audit and collection process before the first interview; and</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="59_1_1002__subsec_1__para_d">
              <num>(d)</num>
              <content>
                <p>allow a taxpayer to be represented at an interview by an attorney or other representative with power of attorney.</p>
              </content>
            </paragraph>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="59_1_1002__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>The commission may not require a taxpayer to bring an attorney or other representative to interviews.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
        </section>
